Program: Outlook
Title: 09/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gfnv5
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 10 May 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: Today, Fedia Hamdi, the council official at the centre of the incident that triggered the people's revolution in Tunisia speaks of her relief at finally being exonerated. Also in the programme, William Ignasius Rettob, the orphaned Indonesian street boy who's turned his life around after surviving sectarian violence and forced labour. And celebrating the moon - another chance for you to send us photos of the moon in your part of the world. Show less